<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="528" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,871,897]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[883,984,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">dissectus</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1046,1152,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">aedeagus</emphasis>
, referring to the distally bifurcated aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
